# .dockerignore
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Files and directories excluded from the Docker build context.
#
# WHY THIS MATTERS:
#   Docker sends the entire build context to the Docker daemon before building.
#   Without .dockerignore, it would send your entire project including:
#     - node_modules (if any)
#     - .git history
#     - vectorstore/ with FAISS indices (could be GBs)
#     - .env with your secrets
#   This slows builds and — critically — .env would be baked into the image.
#
# RULE: exclude anything that shouldn't be in the final image.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── CRITICAL: Never bake secrets into images ──────────────────────────────────
.env
*.env

# ── User data (lives in Docker volumes, not in the image) ────────────────────
vectorstore/
data/

# ── Python cache ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo
*.pyd
.pytest_cache/
*.egg-info/
dist/
build/

# ── Virtual environments ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
venv/
.venv/
env/

# ── Git history (not needed in the image) ─────────────────────────────────────
.git/
.github/

# ── IDE files ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.vscode/
.idea/
*.DS_Store

# ── Documentation (not needed at runtime) ─────────────────────────────────────
README.md
*.md
docs/

# ── Test files ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
tests/
test_*.py

# ── Other Docker files (no need to copy these into themselves) ────────────────
Dockerfile*
docker-compose*
.dockerignore
